  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hereditary haemorrhagic telangiectasia is a disease inherited as an autosomal dominant
      disease. Analysing DNA from affected and unaffected family members allows us to identify the
      location of disease genes by linkage analysis. Sequencing genes in the interval identified by
      linkage analysis allows us to identify which precise gene is mutated. Further functional
      studies can then determine why the mutations in that gene cause the disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
